## Contracts

Search for size-chart data in any browser-visible form: HTML table, page text, modal, rendered widget, PDF, image, embedded asset, product image, help section, FAQ section, Q&A section, seller answer, product details, or size recommendation block. These forms are universal; source types differ only by authority, location, and applicability boundaries.

Read stage input from the Stage prompt context path before starting discovery.

## Persistent State

Treat source discovery as a bounded workflow, not a best-effort search. Derive the source_discover stage directory from the Stage prompt context path, then read the SourceSurfaceInventory schema from sibling `state.schema.json` and build one canonical source-surface inventory state artifact named `state.json` in that same stage directory. The canonical inventory must conform to that generated schema. `url_list` is the only URL inventory list; each URL state is owned only by that URL's `state` field. `table_list` is the only table inventory list; each table state is owned only by that table's `state` field. Update that canonical inventory on every retry before handoff; overwrite the canonical state artifact so verification sees the completed state. attempt-only inventory artifacts are allowed only as extra diagnostics and must not replace the canonical inventory verified by the workflow.

Every evidence path string in the canonical inventory must reference an actually saved artifact path in the current run. Do not invent, rename, translate, or preserve planned evidence paths. Evidence path strings must not contain leading or trailing whitespace. Before handoff, ensure every evidence path listed in state.json points to an existing result-relative path. If a page is blocked or unavailable, save the blocker evidence first and reference that saved artifact; otherwise omit the evidence path and explain the absence in the rejection reason.

Use evidence_write_target.filesystem_path for explicit browser artifact filenames. Use evidence_write_target.artifact_path for evidence references written to state.json.

